HEADWORD: Shedding
<hw>Shed"ding</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of shedding, separating, or casting off or out; <as>as, the
<ex>shedding</ex> of blood</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is shed, or cast off.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Wordsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

